info.headline: Special Weather Statement issued September 26 at 5:49PM EDT by NWS Jacksonville
info.description: ...STRONG THUNDERSTORMS WILL IMPACT SOUTHEASTERN MARION AND SOUTHEASTERN PUTNAM COUNTIES THROUGH 615 PM EDT... At 549 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along a line extending from near Fruitland to Moss Bluff. Movement was northeast at 10 mph. HAZARD...Wind gusts around 40 mph and minor flooding due to heavy rainfall. SOURCE...Radar indicated. IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around unsecured objects. Minor flooding due to heavy rainfall is possible. Locations impacted include... Crescent City, Juniper Springs, Salt Springs, Ocklawaha, Moss Bluff, and Georgetown. MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH
info.instruction: If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
